{
  "text": "In [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] , the same problem is afforded and effectively solved by building, at each sample time, all the possible solutions to the localization problem and selecting the most appropriate by minimizing a proper cost function. Outstanding experimental results are presented in different scenarios; moreover, the use of surface test vehicles equipped with GPS gives also ground truth data. The work [CITATION_3] , however, does not address observability issues. In the same paper the EKF (Extended Kalman Filter) is not used due to the possible presence of outliers in the measurements that, however, where not experienced in the given tests.",
  "correct_citation": {
